did.abstract: These are the official archives of Andover Theological Seminary, a seminary with Congregational roots that affiliated with the Newton Theological Institution in 1965 to become Andover Newton Theological School.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Andover Theological Seminary was founded in 1807. The origin of the school can be traced to Phillips Academy, which was established in 1778 at Andover, Massachusetts. Specific instruction in divinity was provided in 1794 when a legacy was received for the support of a professor of divinity. In 1807, additional funds made possible the founding of a separate department of divinity. The following year, the theological institution known as Andover Theological Seminary was opened for instruction. In 1907 the Seminary transferred to Harvard University. In 1931 the Seminary transferred to Newton Centre, and became affiliated with Newton Theological Institution to form Andover Newton Theological School. In 1965 the two schools formally merged.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: These are the official archives of Andover Theological Seminary, a seminary with Congregational roots that affiliated with the Newton Theological Institution in 1965 to become Andover Newton Theological School. The archives of the Andover Theological Seminary are organized according to its governance and structure. The records have been maintained in the order in which they were received from Andover Newton Theological School.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into eleven series: I. Boards of Trustees and Visitors, II. Faculty, III. Students, IV. Alumni, V. Financial, VI. Legal, VII. Library, VIII. History, IX. Images, X. Publications, XI. Related Organizations.
